 Detectives from the South African Police Service in Storms River are investigating a case of culpable homicide following a fatal accident that took place on the N2 highway at about 08:20 on Monday morning. "It is alleged that a 60-year-old male was traveling on the N2 (close to Hermanuskraal) with a white Mitsubishi Triton Ldv, when he allegedly lost control over the vehicle and it overturned," said police spokesperson, Captain gerda Swart. "The 60-year-old man succumbed from his injuries. "Six other passengers were taken for medical treatment." She said that the name of the deceased will be released after formal identification was done. 